<Project Sdk="Dalamud.NET.Sdk/15.0.0">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <Author>LastOnionKnight</Author>
    <Name>Tonberry Tactics</Name>
    <InternalName>GearGoblin</InternalName>
    <AssemblyVersion>0.6.6.1</AssemblyVersion>
    <FileVersion>0.6.6.1</FileVersion>
    <Version>0.6.6.1</Version>
    <!-- v0.6.6.1 — first polish pass on the Character tab introduced in
         v0.6.6.0. Replaces the plain-text StatsStrip with the card-based
         layout per Claude Design v0.2.0: horizontal grid, per-stat cards
         with label / value / derived-effect lines, border swap on speed
         stats above the 420 baseline, Cinzel + Press Start 2P typography
         pulled from the existing FontAtlasManager. Crafter / Gatherer
         classes now render a "Battle stats not applicable" line instead
         of the misleading 420/420 placeholder values the game returns.
         Bundles BUG-003 closeout — MeldOptimizer.cs now skips audits for
         materia with unrecognized stat types (Substat.None) instead of
         throwing KeyNotFoundException on the totals lookup. Defensive
         try/catch in CharacterTab.DrawMateriaAdvisor still wraps the
         call as belt-and-suspenders.

         Visual polish work continues across v0.6.6.x — CharacterHero
         portrait/bracket treatment in v0.6.6.2, ranked advisor rows
         with gain badges in v0.6.6.3, striped gear table in v0.6.6.4.
         StatusPanelInjector remains shipped through the v0.6.6.x line
         for backward compat — deprecation in v0.6.7, removal in v0.7.0. -->
    <MinimumDalamudVersion>15.0.0</MinimumDalamudVersion>
    <Punchline>BiS planner, Materia Advisor, and round-trip optimizer for FFXIV. The in-game half of Tonberry Tactics; coexists with CharacterPanelRefined.</Punchline>
    <Description>In-game half of Tonberry Tactics. v0.6.6.1 lands the first Character-tab polish pass — card-based StatsStrip per the Claude Design v0.2.0 spec, with per-stat cards (label / value / derived effect / optional next-tier hint), Cinzel + Press Start 2P typography from the existing font atlas, border swap on speed stats above the 420 baseline, and a "Battle stats not applicable" path for Crafter / Gatherer classes. Closes BUG-003 (MeldOptimizer KeyNotFoundException on materia with unrecognized stat types — now skipped quietly instead of throwing). Visual polish continues incrementally across v0.6.6.x: CharacterHero next, then advisor rows, then gear table. Core and Web at v0.6.6.1 lockstep (version-only).</Description>
    <RepoUrl>https://github.com/LastOnionKnight/GearGoblin</RepoUrl>
    <Tags>gear;bis;materia;etro;xivgear;raid;advisor;cpr;character-panel;tonberry-tactics</Tags>

    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
    <LangVersion>latest</LangVersion>
    <AllowUnsafeBlocks>true</AllowUnsafeBlocks>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <!-- v0.4.7.1: brand artwork shipped alongside the DLL. Dalamud's SDK
       picks these up automatically via the Content glob and includes them
       in the plugin's install directory; runtime resolves via
       PluginInterface.AssemblyLocation.Directory + "Assets/" (see
       Services/BrandResources.cs). -->
  <ItemGroup>
    <Content Include="Assets\**\*.png">
      <CopyToOutputDirectory>PreserveNewest</CopyToOutputDirectory>
      <Pack>true</Pack>
    </Content>
  </ItemGroup>

  <!-- v0.6.0: custom .ttf fonts for IFontAtlas Phase 2. Same copy
       discipline as the brand artwork — runtime resolves the directory
       via PluginInterface.AssemblyLocation.Directory + "Assets/Fonts/"
       (see Theme/FontAtlasManager.cs). -->
  <ItemGroup>
    <Content Include="Assets\Fonts\*.ttf">
      <CopyToOutputDirectory>PreserveNewest</CopyToOutputDirectory>
      <Pack>true</Pack>
    </Content>
  </ItemGroup>

  <!--
    v0.6.3: ProjectReference to the shared GearGoblin.Core library.
    Path assumes the standard sibling-of-grandparent layout:

        D:\GearGoblin-Core-v0.1\GearGoblin.Core\        (Core, this reference's target)
        D:\GearGoblin-v0.1\GearGoblin\                  (this project)
        D:\TonberryTactics-workspace\TonberryTactics\   (web, mirrors this same reference)
  -->
  <ItemGroup>
    <ProjectReference Include="..\..\GearGoblin-Core-v0.1\GearGoblin.Core\GearGoblin.Core.csproj" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
